Hi Wladimir,

You can not find the checkinstall command because it is not installed.
Open a shell and after became superuser write:

apt-get install checkinstall

and after always as root (go to the cantera-1.6.0 directory) and type

checkinstall.

Be sure to have set correctly your paths if you use a local installation.
I&#39;ve always use the /usr/local path without problem.
If you use checkinstall you can easily remove the package in a second 
moment using the command (alway as root):

apt-get remove cantera-1.6.0

I hope this help.

Michele



